translation_text: "Didn't I say she was not guilty?"
The Prince and Claudio also blamed her for a mistake you heard about. But Margaret was partly to blame too, even though she didn't mean to be.
I'm happy that everything turned out so well.
"I feel the same way, because my beliefs make me confront young Claudio about it."

"Alright, daughter and all you ladies, go into a room by yourselves. When I call for you, come back wearing masks. The Prince and Claudio promised to visit me by now. You know what to do, brother: you need to be a father to your brother's daughter and give her to young Claudio."
"I will do it with a steady face."
Friar, I need your help, I believe.
"What to do, sir?"
"To tie me down or set me free -- it's one or the other. Mr. Leonato, it's true, your niece looks at me kindly."
That eye my daughter gave her is really true.
"I love her back with my eyes."
"I think you saw that from me, from Claudio and the Prince. But what do you want?"
Your answer is confusing, but I want to ask if you agree to let us get married today in a good and honorable way. I would like your help with this, kind friar.
"I care about what you like."
"Here comes the Prince and Claudio, and I’m here to help."
"Good morning to everyone here."
Good morning, Prince; good morning, Claudio; we are here for you. Have you decided to marry my brother's daughter today?
I will keep my thoughts to myself even if she were from Ethiopia.
"Bring her out, brother; the priest is ready. Antonio comes back with the ladies wearing masks."
"Which girl should I take?"
"This is her, and I give her to you."
"Then she belongs to me. Please, let me see your face."
"No, you can't do that until you hold her hand, in front of this priest, and promise to marry her."
Hold my hand in front of this priest. I can be your husband if you want me to be.
"When I was alive, I was your other wife; and when you loved, you were my other husband."
"Another hero!"
"There's no doubt about it: One Hero has died in shame, but I am still alive, and as sure as I'm alive, I am still a girl."
"The old Hero! Hero who is gone!"
She died, my lord, but people kept talking badly about her.
I can explain all this surprise later, after the wedding is over, and then I'll tell you about Hero's death. For now, let's just act like this is normal and go to the chapel.
"Calm down, friar. Which one is Beatrice?"
"I go by that name. What do you want?"
"Don't you love me?"
"No, not at all, that's just how it should be."
"Then your uncle, the Prince, and Claudio have been tricked -- they all said you did."
"Don't you love me?"
"Honestly, no, not at all."
So, my cousin, Margaret and Ursula are very mistaken because they promised you did.
"They promised that you were really worried about me."
They promised that you were almost dead because of me.
"It doesn't matter. So, you don't love me?"
"No, really, just as a friendly reward."
Come on, cousin, I know you like the guy.
"I swear he loves her because here’s a note he wrote himself, a clumsy poem made just for Beatrice."
"And here's another letter, written by my cousin and taken from her pocket, showing how much she cares for Benedick."
It's amazing! Our hands are against our hearts. Come, I want you, but I feel sorry for you.
I won't say no to you, but today I agree because you convinced me, and partly to help you stay alive since I heard you were very sick.
"Shh! I will kiss you to make you quiet."
"How are you, 'Benedick, the married man'?"

I'll tell you something, Prince; no one can make me lose my good mood. Claudio, I thought about fighting you, but since you're going to be my family, let's stay friends and love my cousin. Come on, let's dance before we get married to cheer ourselves and our wives up.
"We'll dance later."
"First, I promise! So, let’s play some music. Prince, you look sad; you should get a wife!"
My lord, your brother John has been caught trying to escape and brought back to Messina with soldiers.
Don't worry about him until tomorrow; I'll come up with some strong punishments for him. Let's play music and dance!
I read in this letter that Don Pedro from Aragon is coming to Messina tonight.
He is really close; he was only about nine miles away when I left him.
I see that Don Pedro has given a lot of respect to a young man from Florence named Claudio.
He really earned it, and Don Pedro remembers it just as much.
Please tell me, has Signior Mountanto come back from the war or not?
"I don't know anyone by that name, lady; there wasn't anyone like that in the army."
"My cousin is talking about Signior Benedick from Padua."
Oh, he's back and just as nice as he always was.
Please tell me, how many has he killed and eaten in these wars? But really, how many has he killed? Because I promised to eat everything he killed.
Honestly, niece, you are being too hard on Benedick, but I’m sure he can handle it.
"He has done a great job, lady, in these battles."
"Don't get the wrong idea about my niece. She and Signior Benedick always have a playful argument whenever they see each other."

Oh no, he doesn't gain anything from that. In our last fight, he lost most of his senses, and now he only has one left to think with. Who is he hanging out with now? He gets a new best friend every month.
He is mostly with the good and honorable Claudio.

Oh no, he will cling to him like a sickness; it's easier to catch than a plague, and the person who gets it goes crazy. God help the good Claudio! If he has fallen for Benedick, it will cost him a lot of money to get over it.
"You will never go crazy, my dear."
"No, not until January is really warm."
"Don Pedro is being approached."
"Hello, Mr. Leonato, are you here to face your problems? People usually try to avoid spending money, but you are dealing with it."
I've never had trouble at home like you bring. When you're gone, sadness stays and joy leaves.
"You hug your responsibility too eagerly. I believe this is your daughter."
Her mom has told me that many times.
"Did you ask her because you were unsure, sir?"
"Mr. Benedick, no, because then you would be acting like a child."
You have it all, Benedick; we can tell what kind of man you are. Truly, the lady is just like her father. Be happy, lady, because you are like a good father.
If Leonato is her father, she wouldn't want to look like him for anything in Messina.
I’m surprised you’re still talking, Benedick; no one is paying attention to you.
"What, my dear Lady Disdain! Are you still alive?"
Can it really be that dislike can go away when she has someone like Benedick to make her feel that way? Even being polite will turn into dislike if you are around her.
Kindness is fake. Everyone loves me except you, and I wish I could feel that I have a kind heart, but honestly, I don’t love anyone.
Women would be very happy because otherwise, they would have to deal with a bad suitor. I'm glad I'm like you; I'd rather listen to my dog bark at a crow than hear a man say he loves me.
I hope you stay that way, so some man won't end up with a scratched face.
Scratching wouldn't make it any worse, and your face is just like that.
"Well, you are a one-of-a-kind teacher."
My words are better than your actions.
I wish my horse could run as fast as you talk, but go your own way, I've finished my part.
I know you well, and you always use a sneaky trick.

That's everything, Leonato. [Turning to everyone.] Claudio and Benedick, my good friend Leonato has invited you all. I told him we would stay here for at least a month, and he really hopes something will keep us here even longer.
"Welcome, my lord! I'm glad to see you made up with your brother, the Prince. I respect you."
"Thank you! I don't say much, but I really appreciate it."
"Would you please go ahead?"
"Let's go together, Leonato, hold my hand."
"Benedick, did you see Signior Leonato's daughter?"
"I didn't pay attention to her, but I saw her."
"Isn't she a shy young girl?"
Are you asking me honestly for my true opinion, or do you want me to speak like a bully towards women?
"No, please talk seriously."

I really think she's not good enough for high praise, too dark for nice compliments, and too small for big praise. The only nice thing I can say is that if she were different, she wouldn't be pretty, and since she's not different, I don't like her.
You think I'm joking: please tell me honestly what you think of her.
"Are you asking about her because you want to buy her?"
"Can the world find something as precious as this?"
"Yes, and a box to put it in."
In my eyes, she is the sweetest girl I've ever seen.

I can still see without glasses, and I don’t see anything like that: there’s her cousin, and she’s much more beautiful than her, just like May is much nicer than December. But I hope you don’t plan to get married, do you?
I would hardly believe myself, even if I promised otherwise, if Hero wanted to marry me.
Has it really come to this? Does no one trust each other anymore? Will I never see an old single man again?
What secret kept you here instead of going to Leonato's?
I wish you would make me tell.
I ask you to be loyal.

Listen, Count Claudio: I can keep a secret like a quiet person, and I want you to believe that; but I promise you, he is in love. With who? That's for you to find out. Notice how brief his answer is: with Hero, Leonato's young daughter.
"If my feelings don't change soon, I hope they never do."
Yes, if you love her, because she is truly deserving.
"I know that I love her."
"I know she is deserving."
I don't understand why she should be loved or why she deserves it, and I can't change my mind about that; I'll stick to it no matter what.
You have always been stubborn and refused to accept what is beautiful.
"And he could only keep his promise if he really wanted to."
I thank my mother for giving me life and raising me. Since I don't want to doubt anyone, I choose not to trust anyone, and because of that, I will stay single.
I will see you, before I die, looking pale because of love.
"I'm feeling angry, sick, or hungry, my lord, but not in love."
If you ever stop believing in this, you'll be a great example of what can go wrong.
"If I do, hang me up like a cat in a bottle and let people shoot at me. Whoever hits me should be patted on the back and called Adam."
In time, even the wild bull learns to accept its burden.

A wild bull might do it, but if smart Benedick ever does, then take the bull's horns and put them on my head, and paint me ugly, with big letters saying, 'Here is a good horse for rent,' and let it say underneath, 'Here you can see Benedick, the married man.'
Take your time. In the meantime, please go to Leonato's house, say hello for me, and tell him I will definitely be there for dinner because he has prepared a lot.
I have just about enough to say for this message, so I'm leaving you now.
My lord, you can help me now. Does Leonato have a son?
"Hero is the only child, and she will inherit everything. Do you love her, Claudio?"

Oh my lord, when you went off to fight, I looked at her like a soldier, appreciating her but focused on my tough job. Now that I'm back, my thoughts of war are gone, and all I can think about is how beautiful young Hero is, reminding me that I liked her before I went to battle.

You will act like a lover soon and bore the listener with too many words. If you love Hero, take care of it, and I will end things with her and her dad so you can have her. I know we will have a party tonight: I will pretend to be you and tell Hero I’m you, and I’ll share my feelings with her. Then I’ll talk to her dad, and in the end, she will be yours. Let’s do this right away.
"Come on, Friar Francis, make it quick: just get to the simple marriage part, and you can explain their roles later."
"Are you here, my lord, to marry this lady?"
"No."
You’re here to marry her, priest.
"Lady, are you here to marry this Count?"
"I will."
"If either of you has a good reason not to get married, please speak up now."
"Do you know anyone, Hero?"
"Nobody, my lord."
"Do you know anyone, Count?"
"I dare say his answer is, 'None.'"
"Please step aside, priest. Father, if you agree: Will you freely give me your daughter?"
"Just as freely, son, as God gave her to me."
"What can I give you in return that is as valuable as this wonderful gift?"
"Nothing, unless you give her back."

Sweet Prince, you teach me to be grateful. Here, Leonato, take her back. Don't give this bad orange to your friend; she only looks like she has honor. Look how she blushes like a girl! Wouldn't you all think she was a girl just by how she looks? But she's not: her blush shows her guilt, not shyness.
"What do you mean, my lord?"
"I don't want to get married or tie my life to someone who is untrustworthy. I never said anything too bold to her, but treated her with honest kindness like a brother would with his sister."
"Did I ever seem different to you?"

Get away from me, fake! I will speak out against you. You look pure like the moon, innocent like a flower bud before it blooms; but you are wilder in your desires than Venus or those spoiled creatures that act on their wild passions.
Is my lord okay if he talks like that?
"Dear Prince, why aren't you talking?"
What should I say? I feel ashamed for trying to connect my good friend to someone unworthy. LEONATO: Am I really hearing this, or is it just a dream?
"Let me ask your daughter one question, and with your caring influence, tell her to answer honestly."
I ask you to do this because you are my child.
Oh God, help me! Why am I in this situation? What kind of questioning is this? CLAUDIO: It's to make you honestly say your name.
"Is that Hero? Who could say anything bad about her?"
Yes, Hero can lose her goodness. Who was the man you talked to last night out your window between midnight and one? If you're a good girl, answer me.
"I didn't talk to anyone at that time, my lord."

"Then you are not a pure girl. Leonato, I'm sorry you have to know this: I swear, my brother and I saw her talking with a bad man at her window last night, and he admitted that they have secretly met many times."

Oh Hero! You would have been such a great person if your beauty matched your thoughts and feelings! But goodbye, you are both good and bad! For you, I will close myself off from love, and I will only think of bad things when I see beauty, and it will never be kind to me again.
"Doesn't anyone have a knife here that I can use?"
faints
"Hey, cousin! Why are you sitting down?"
Come on, let's go. These things make her feel very sad.
"How is the lady?"
I think she's dead. Help me, uncle! Hero! Oh, Hero! Uncle! Mr. Benedick! Friar!
Oh Fate, please don’t be so harsh! Death is the best way to hide her shame that anyone could hope for.
"Hey there, cousin Hero!"
"Don't worry, lady."
"Are you looking up?"
"Yes, why shouldn't she?"

"Why? Doesn't everything on earth blame her? Could she deny what is in her blood? Don't live, Hero, don't open your eyes; if I thought you wouldn't die quickly, I would hurt you with my words. Am I sad that I only had one? Did I complain about how nature made you? Oh, having you was too much! Why did I have you? Why were you always so beautiful to me?"
"Sir, please be patient. I'm so amazed that I don't know what to say."
Oh no, my cousin is being wrongly accused!
"Did you sleep in the same bed with her last night?"
"No, really, not at all; but until last night, I have been sleeping next to her for a whole year."
It's true, it's true! What was once locked up tight is now stronger! Could the two princes and Claudio, who loved her so much, really say bad things about her while crying?

Listen to me for a moment; I've seen the lady blush a thousand times, and there's a fire in her eyes that can burn away the mistakes these princes think about her. Call me foolish if I'm wrong, but I believe this sweet lady is innocent of any wrongdoing.
Brother, it can't be. You see that the only good thing she has left is that she won’t lie and make her situation worse; she doesn’t deny it.
"Lady, who is the man you are being blamed for?"

"Those who say I did something wrong know the truth; I don’t know anyone like that. Oh, my father, if you can prove that I talked to anyone at the wrong time or argued with anyone last night, then you can reject me, hate me, or even hurt me!"
The princes are acting very strangely.
Two of them really care about honor; and if they make a mistake here, John the bastard is the one who does bad things.
"I don't know. If they are telling the truth about her, I'll hurt her; but if they are lying about her, the most arrogant one will pay for it."
Wait a moment, and listen to my advice. Keep your daughter hidden for now and tell everyone she has died. Act sad and put up a memorial for her.
What will happen now? What will this cause?

If she is treated well, people will feel sorry for her instead of blaming her. When she dies right after being accused, everyone will feel sad and forgive her. We often don't appreciate what we have until it's gone, and Claudio will realize he was wrong to accuse her when he hears she died because of it. Let’s hope everything turns out better than I can predict.
Mr. Leonato, let the priest help you; even though you know I care a lot for the Prince and Claudio, I promise to handle this matter quietly and fairly, just like your soul should care for your body.
I am so sad that even the tiniest thing can affect me.
It's agreed. Come, my lady, you must let go to truly live; this wedding day might just be delayed; be patient and hang in there.
"Beatrice, have you been crying this whole time?"
Yes, and I will cry for a little while longer.
"I don't want that."
"You don't have to worry, I'm doing it because I want to."
I really think your nice cousin has been treated unfairly.
"Oh, how much I would owe to the man who helps her!"
"Is there a way to show such friendship?"
It's a fair way, but I have no friend like that.
"Can a man do it?"
It's a job for a man, but not for you.
"I love you more than anything else in the world -- isn't that odd?"
It's as strange as something I can't explain. I could say I love nothing more than you, but you shouldn't believe me; still, I'm not lying. I'm sorry for my cousin.
"I swear by my sword, Beatrice, you love me."
Don't promise and then take it back.
I will promise that you love me, and I will make anyone who says I don't love you regret it.
Aren't you going to take back what you said?
"I can't think of any way to make it better. I really love you."
"Well then, I hope God forgives me!"
"What did you do wrong, sweet Beatrice?"
You stopped me at a good time; I was just about to say that I love you.
"Do it with all your heart."
I love you so much that I have no love left to argue against it.
Come, tell me what you want me to do for you.
"Make sure Claudio is dead!"
"Ha, not for anything in the world!"
"You hurt me by refusing to admit it. Goodbye."
"Wait, sweet Beatrice."
I'm not really here, even though I am; you don't love me, so please let me leave.
Beatrice - -
"I promise, I will go."
"Let's be friends first."
You find it easier to be my friend than to fight my enemy.
"Is Claudio your enemy?"
Isn't he a terrible villain for talking badly about my relative? I wish I were a man! I would confront him publicly and show everyone what he did. I would be so angry!
"Listen to me, Beatrice - -"
Sweet Hero! She has been hurt, she has been lied about, and she is in trouble.
"Hit —"

Oh, princes and nobles! I wish I were a man for his sake, or that I had a friend who would be a man for me! But being a man has turned into just being polite, and bravery is now just talk. A man who only lies and swears is not really brave. I can’t become a man just by wishing, so I will suffer as a woman.
Wait, dear Beatrice. I truly love you.
Show your love for me in a different way than just making promises.
Do you believe in your heart that Count Claudio has hurt Hero?
Yes, as sure as I have thoughts or feelings.

That's enough! I'm busy, and I will confront him. I'll kiss your hand now and then I have to go. Claudio will owe me a big explanation. Think of me as you hear about me. Go cheer up your cousin; I have to say she has died: goodbye.

I really wonder how a man can laugh at others for being foolish in love, yet end up being just as foolish himself, like Claudio. He used to love simple things, but now he only cares about fancy clothes and music. He used to speak clearly like a soldier, but now he talks in a confusing way. I want a woman who has everything: beauty, wisdom, and kindness, or I won't want her at all.
"Come, should we listen to this music?"
"Yes, my good lord."
"Do you see where Benedick is hiding?"
"Oh, that's fine, my lord."
"Come on, Balthasar, let's listen to that song again."

Don't sigh anymore, ladies. Men have always been tricky. They can't stay true to one thing. So, don't be sad; let them go and be happy. Turn your sad songs into cheerful ones. Stop singing sad tunes; they only bring you down. Men have always been this way since the beginning of time.
"Honestly, that was a nice song. Come here, Leonato. What did you say today about your niece Beatrice being in love with Benedick?"
The bird is sitting. I never thought that lady would love any man.
"No, me neither, but it's really surprising that she loves Signior Benedick so much, even though she always acted like she hated him."
I promise, my lord, I don’t know what to think, but she loves him so much that it’s hard to understand.
"Maybe she is just pretending."
"Yes, that's probably true."
Oh God! Pretend feelings? No one has ever faked love as well as she shows it.
"What feelings is she showing?"
"What will happen, my lord? She will make you sit — you heard my daughter say how."
"She really did."
How is that possible? You surprise me; I would have thought she couldn't be hurt by love at all.
I would have bet it was true, my lord, especially about Benedick.
"keep himself in such respect."
"Has she told Benedick that she likes him?"
"No, and she promises she never will: that's what makes her unhappy."
It's true, your daughter says: "Should I, who have often treated him with disrespect, write to him that I love him?"
She says this now as she starts to write to him, because she'll get up twenty times at night and sit in her nightgown until she finishes a letter: my daughter tells us everything.

She falls to her knees, cries, and hits her heart, pulls her hair, prays, and curses: "Oh, sweet Benedick! Please give me strength!" LEONATO: Yes, my daughter says that, and she's so overwhelmed that sometimes I worry she might hurt herself.
It would be better if Benedick heard about it from someone else, if she won't tell him.
"Why? He would just make fun of it and hurt the poor lady even more."
"It would be kind to hang him. She's a really nice lady, and everyone knows she's good."
"And she is very smart."
"In every way except for loving Benedick."
I feel sorry for her because I have a good reason, since I am her uncle and take care of her.
Please tell Benedick about it and see what he says.
"Do you think it would be good?"
Hero believes she will definitely die because she says she will if he doesn't love her, and she will die before telling him her feelings, and she would rather die than change her usual stubbornness.
She is doing well: if she offers her love, he might reject it because, as you all know, he has a mean spirit.
He is a very nice man.
He really looks happy on the outside.
"Honestly, I think it's very smart."
He really does show some clever ideas.
"I think he is brave."
I'm sorry for your niece. Should we go find Benedick and tell him she loves him?
"Don't tell him, my lord; let her handle it with good advice."
"No way, that's not possible; she might get really sad first."

"Okay, we'll hear more about it from your daughter later; let's take a break for now. I really like Benedick, and I wish he would think about how he doesn't deserve such a wonderful lady. LEONATO: My lord, shall we go? Dinner is ready."
"Women will talk. It will be fun when they share their thoughts about each other, but let's just ask her to bring him in for dinner."

This can't be a trick: they talked seriously, and they got the truth from Hero. They seem to feel sorry for her; it looks like she really loves. Love me? Of course, I need to love her back. I never thought I would marry, but I shouldn't act proud: those who hear bad things about them and can fix it are lucky. Honestly, it doesn't make her any smarter or show she's foolish, because I'm going to be really in love with her. I might say some funny things about not wanting to marry since I've complained about it for so long, but doesn't that feeling change? When I said I would stay single, I didn't think I'd live to see marriage. Here comes Beatrice. Wow, she's beautiful! I can see signs that she loves me too.
I don’t want to, but I have to ask you to come in for dinner.
Thank you, lovely Beatrice, for all your hard work.
I didn’t work hard for your thanks, just like you didn’t work hard to thank me; if it had been hard, I wouldn’t have come.
"Do you enjoy the message?"
You’re as brave as a tiny piece of food on a knife that could choke a bird. You’re not strong enough, goodbye.

"Ha! I was asked to invite you to dinner even though I didn’t want to. I didn’t work hard for your thanks, just like you didn’t work hard to thank me. If I don’t feel sorry for her, I’m a bad person."
Please, dear Mistress Margaret, do something nice for me by helping me talk to Beatrice.
Will you write me a poem about how beautiful I am?
"You are so wonderful, Margaret, that no one alive can match you, because you truly deserve it."
"I will bring Beatrice to you, who I believe can walk."
"And so I will come."
"Sweet Beatrice, would you come when I called you?"
"Yes, sir, I will leave when you tell me to."
"Oh, just wait until then!"
"Now I've said what I needed to say; goodbye. But before I leave, I want to know what happened between you and Claudio."
"Just bad words, and then I will kiss you."
Bad words are just bad air, and bad air is just bad breath, which is unpleasant; so I will leave without a kiss.

"You've scared him so much that he's not thinking straight because you're so clever. But I have to say, Claudio has accepted my challenge, and I need to hear from him soon, or I'll call him a coward. Now tell me, what was it about my bad qualities that made you fall in love with me?"
"They all worked together to be so bad that they won't let anything good mix with them. But which good thing about me made you love me at first?"
"Being in love is hard! I really do suffer because I love you even though I don't want to."
Even though you don’t want to, I believe. Oh, poor heart! If you hurt it for me, I’ll hurt it for you, because I can’t love what my friend hates.
You and I are too smart to try to get along nicely.
It's not shown in this confession; only one out of twenty smart people will say good things about themselves.
"I've talked enough about how great I am, and I know I am. Now, how is your cousin?"
"Really sick."
"And how are you?"
"Very sick too."
"Serve God, love me, and improve yourself. I'll leave you now because someone is coming quickly."
You need to go to your uncle. It's been shown that Lady Hero was wrongly accused, and the Prince and Claudio were really hurt, and Don John is the one who did it and has run away. Will you come now?
"Will you go listen to this news, sir?"
I will live in your heart, die in your arms, and be remembered in your eyes; and also, I will go with you to your uncle's.
"I'm just waiting until your marriage is complete, and then I'm going to Aragon."
Friends, I am not the same as I used to be.
"I think you look sadder."
Old man, come talk with me privately; I have some important things to say that I don't want others to hear.
"I swear, I can't argue with him about Beatrice."
That's right. Hero and Margaret have helped Beatrice, so the two bears won't fight when they see each other.
"Hello, my lord and brother! May God keep you safe!"
"Good day, brother."
"If you have some free time, I would like to talk to you."
"Just between us?"
"If you don’t mind, I need to talk about something that involves Count Claudio."
"What's wrong?"
"Are you getting married tomorrow?"
"You know he does."
"I don't know if he will understand what I know."
"If there’s any problem, please let me know."
You might think I don't love you, but you'll see later. My brother cares for you and has helped with your upcoming marriage, but it's a waste of effort.
"What's wrong?"
"I came here to tell you that the lady is not faithful."
"Who, Hero?"
"She is Hero, the one everyone loves."
"Unfaithful?"

It's hard to describe how bad she is. I could say she's even worse; think of a worse name for her and I'll agree. Don't be surprised just yet: come with me tonight, and if you really love her, marry her tomorrow; but it would be better for your reputation if you reconsider.
"Is this really true?"
"I won't believe it."
If you’re not sure you can believe what you see, don’t say you know it. If you want to come with me, I’ll show you what you need to see, and then you can decide what to do next.
If I see anything tonight that makes me think I shouldn't marry her tomorrow, I will embarrass her in front of everyone.
"I tried to win her for you, and now I will help you make her look bad."
I won't say anything bad about her until you see it for yourselves. Stay calm until midnight, and then we'll see what happens.
"Oh, what a terrible day!"
"Oh, what a strange trouble!"
"Oh, what a disaster was avoided! You'll say the same after you see what happens next."

"Ursula, when Beatrice arrives, we should only talk about Benedick as we walk here. When I mention him, you should say nice things about him, and I will tell you how much Benedick loves Beatrice. Let’s start now; here comes Beatrice, trying to listen to us."
The best fishing is watching the fish swim with their shiny tails in the water and eagerly eat the tricky bait. So, we are trying to win Beatrice's heart, don’t worry about what I will say.
"No, really, Ursula, she is too proud."
"Are you really sure that Benedick loves Beatrice completely?"
"My fiancé, the Prince, says so."
"Did they ask you to tell her about it, ma'am?"
They asked me to tell her, but I convinced them that if they cared for Benedick, they should let him deal with his feelings and not tell Beatrice.
"Why did you do that? Doesn't the gentleman deserve a nice bed just like Beatrice?"

Oh, god of love! I know he deserves as much as any man can get, but Nature didn't make a woman's heart prouder than Beatrice's. She looks down on everything with disdain and thinks very highly of herself, so much that nothing else seems strong to her. She can't love or feel any affection because she loves herself too much.
I think so; it wouldn't be good for her to know he loves her, or she might make fun of it.
You're right. I've never seen a man who is wise, noble, or handsome that she doesn't criticize. She always sees the worst in every man and never appreciates honesty and goodness like they deserve.
Of course, complaining like that is not good.

"But who would be brave enough to tell her? If I said something, she would just laugh at me and make me feel small. So, I’ll let Benedick quietly suffer in silence; it’s better than being made fun of."
"Go ahead and tell her; listen to what she says."
"No; I will go to Benedick and tell him to fight his feelings. I'll come up with some truthful lies to make my cousin look bad because you never know how much a bad word can ruin someone's love."
Oh, please don't treat your cousin so badly! She can't be so foolish as to turn down such a great guy like Benedick.
"He is the only man in Italy, except for my dear friend Claudio."
"When are you getting married, ma'am?"
"Why, every day is like tomorrow! Come inside; I'll show you some clothes and get your advice on which is best for me to wear tomorrow."

What’s happening to my ears? Is this real? Am I really being judged for being proud and scornful? Goodbye, pride and arrogance! Benedick, keep loving me, and I will return your love, calming my wild heart for you. If you love me, my kindness will encourage you to join our hearts together; others say you deserve it, and I believe it more than what they say.
"Is everyone here?"
"Oh, get a stool and a cushion for the gravekeeper. Gravekeeper, who are the bad guys?"
Yes, that's me and my partner.
"No, that's true, we need to look at the show. But who are the people that need to be checked? They should come in front of the police officer."
"Yes, let them come to me. What's your name, friend?"
"Drunkard."
"Please write down 'Borachio'. Yours, sir?"
"I am a man of good character, sir, and my name is Conrade."
"Write down, 'Mr. Conrade.' Do you serve God? CONRADE/ BORACHIO: Yes, sir, we hope so."
You guys have already shown that you are not much better than liars, and soon people will really think that. What do you have to say for yourselves?
"Well, sir, we say we are nobody."
He's a clever and funny guy, I promise, but I will hang out with him. Come here, young man, I need to tell you something; people think you are dishonest.
Sir, I tell you we are nobody.
"Did you write that there are none?"
"Officer, you're not doing it right; you need to bring in the guards who are the ones accusing them."
Yes, that's the quickest way. Let the guards come out. Friends, I ask you, in the Prince's name, to blame these men.
This man said, sir, that Don John's brother was a bad guy.
"Write down that Prince John is a bad guy. That's a lie to call a prince's brother a bad guy."
"Mr. Constable -"
"Please, friend, be quiet; I don't like the way you look, I swear."
"What else did you hear him say?"
He got a thousand coins from Don John for falsely accusing Lady Hero.
It's just plain stealing, like always.
"Yes, it really is."
"What else, friend?"
Count Claudio planned to shame Hero in front of everyone and not marry her.
Oh, you bad person! You will be punished forever for this.
"What more?"
"This is everything."

"Listen, everyone, you can't deny this. Prince John has secretly run away this morning; Hero was accused like this, denied it, and then died from the sadness. Constable, tie these men up and take them to Leonato; I'll go ahead and tell him what happened."
"Come, let them think what they want."
"Let them be taken care of by others."
"Get lost, fool!"
Oh my gosh, where's the grave digger? Tell him to write down 'the Prince's silly officer'. Come on, tie them up. You naughty rascal!
Go away! You're a fool, you're a fool.

"Don't you see my position? Don't you see my age? I wish he were here to call me a fool! But remember, I know I'm a fool, even if it’s not written down. No, you bad person, you pretend to be good, and I’ll prove it. I’m smart, I have a job, I have a home, and I’m as good-looking as anyone in Messina, and I know the law. Take him away! I wish I had been called a fool!"
"Why are you so sad, my lord?"
The situation is so big that it makes sadness feel endless.
"You should listen to good advice."
"And when I hear it, what good thing does it bring?"
"If there's no quick fix, then at least be patient and endure."

I can't pretend to be someone I'm not: I have to be sad when I'm sad, and I won't laugh at jokes I don't find funny; I'll eat when I'm hungry, and I won't wait for anyone else; I'll sleep when I'm tired, and I won't worry about what others are doing; I'll laugh when I'm happy, and I won't bother anyone else.

Yes, but you shouldn't show everything until you can do it freely. You've recently had a conflict with your brother, and now he's being nice to you again, so you can only truly succeed if you create a good situation for yourself. You need to make things right for your own benefit.

I would rather be a nasty weed than a pretty flower in his favor, and I’d rather be disliked by everyone than pretend to steal love from someone. I may not be a nice person, but I’m honest about it. If I could speak freely, I would; if I had the freedom, I would do what I want. For now, let me be who I am and don’t try to change me.
Can't you find a way to use your unhappiness?
"I use it all by myself. Who's coming? What's the news, Borachio?"

"I just came from a big dinner. Your brother the Prince is having a fancy time with Leonato, and I have news about a planned wedding. DON JOHN: Can we use this to cause trouble? What kind of fool wants to marry someone who brings chaos?"
"Yes, it belongs to your brother."
"Who is the wonderful Claudio?"
"Even him."
"Look at that nice young man! Who is he? Which way is he looking?"
"Yes, Hero is the daughter and heir of Leonato."
Let's go there; this might make me even more unhappy. That young upstart has taken all the credit for my failure. If I can stop him in any way, I'll feel lucky. Are you both sure you will help me?
"I'll stand by you until the end, my lord."
Shall we go see what needs to be done?
We'll wait for you, sir.
"Are you honest and good people?"
Yes, or else it would be a shame if they didn't get saved, both in body and spirit.
"No, that would be too nice a punishment for them if they cared about being chosen to watch over the Prince."
"Okay, tell them what to do, neighbor Dogberry."
People think you are the silliest and best person to be the watchman, so you get to carry the lantern. Your job is to catch any troublemakers and tell them to stop in the Prince's name.
"What if someone doesn't agree?"
"Then just ignore him and let him leave, and quickly gather the others to thank God you're done with a trickster."
"If he won't obey when asked, he's not one of the Prince's people."
It's true, they should only deal with the Prince's people. Also, you must be quiet in the streets because it's okay for the guards to talk, but it's really annoying and not acceptable.
We'd rather sleep than talk; we know how to keep watch.
"Why do you talk like an old, silent guard? I don’t understand how sleeping could be a problem."
If you see a thief, you might think he’s not a good person because of your job, and it’s better to stay away from people like him to keep your own honesty.
"If we know he's a thief, shouldn't we catch him?"

You can do it if you want, but I believe that if you get too close to bad people, you'll get dirty too. The best thing for you to do if you catch a thief is to let him reveal his true self and leave your group.
"You've always been known as a kind man, my friend."
I really wouldn’t want to hurt a dog, let alone a good person.
"This is the end of the order: you, officer, need to bring the Prince himself."
Good night, everyone. If anything important happens, let me know. Keep your secrets and your friends' secrets, and good night. Come on, friend.
Okay, friends, we know what we need to do: let’s sit on the church bench until two o'clock, and then we can go to bed.
One more thing, good neighbors. Please keep an eye on Signior Leonato's door tonight because there's a lot going on for the wedding tomorrow. Goodbye! Stay alert, I ask you.
"What, Conrade!"
"Conrade, I'm talking to you!"
"I'm right here, friend. Now go ahead and tell your story."
Come stand close under this roof because it's drizzling, and I will tell you everything like a real drunk person.
So, just so you know, Don John has given me a thousand ducats.
Can any bad thing be so precious?
You should ask if it's even possible for a bad person to be so wealthy; because when rich bad people need help from poor ones, the poor can ask for whatever they want.

I want you to know that tonight I tried to win over Margaret, who is Hero's friend, by calling her Hero. I should first tell you how the Prince, Claudio, and my master Don John saw this nice moment from a distance in the orchard.
"And they thought Margaret was Hero?"

The Prince and Claudio both saw her, but my master knew she was actually Margaret. Claudio got really angry and promised to confront her the next morning at the temple, where he would embarrass her in front of everyone and send her home without a husband.
"We ask you in the Prince's name, stop!"
Get the right police officer; we have found the most serious case of bad behavior that anyone has ever seen in our community.
"Hey, everyone!"
"Please don't say anything, just come with us."
"We are likely to be something valuable."
"We'll do what you say, I promise."
If you keep this up, you will hurt yourself, and it's not smart to make your sadness worse.

Don't give me advice, and don't let anyone comfort me unless they understand my pain. Bring me a father who loved his child as much as I love mine, and ask him to talk about being patient; because, brother, people can give advice about sadness that they don't actually feel. So, don't give me advice: my sadness is too strong for that.
Don't blame yourself for everything; let those who hurt you feel the pain too.
"You’re right; I will do that. My heart tells me Hero is being lied about, and Claudio will find out, along with the Prince and everyone else who is treating her badly."
Here comes the Prince and Claudio quickly.
"Good day, good day."
"Hello to both of you."
"Listen, my lords - -"
"We need to hurry, Leonato."
"Are you in a hurry, my lord? Goodbye then! Are you really rushing? It doesn't matter."
"Please, don't argue with us, kind old man."
"If he could fix things by fighting, some of us would stay quiet."
"Who hurts him?"
You’re being unfair to me, you liar! Don’t reach for your sword; I’m not afraid of you.
I swear, my hand didn't mean to scare you. Honestly, my hand was just trying to help my sword.

Stop joking around, man! Listen, Claudio, you have hurt my innocent child and me. You have lied about her, and your lies have deeply affected her. She is now buried with her family, in a place where no one has ever spoken badly about her, except for your cruel words!
"My bad behavior?"
"It's yours, Claudio; I mean it."
"You’re not being fair, old man."
"Sir, I will show it on him if he is brave enough."
Go away! I don’t want to be with you.
"You've killed my child; if you kill me too, you'll be killing a man."
He will kill two of us, but that doesn't matter; let him kill one first. If he wins me, he can have me. Come on, boy, follow me! I'll teach you a lesson, I promise.
"Brother —"
Be calm. God knows I loved my niece, and she is dead, falsely accused by bad people.
"Brother Antony - -"
"Come on, it doesn't matter; don't get involved, I'll handle this."
Both of you, we won't take up your time. I'm really sorry about your daughter's death, but I promise she was only accused of things that were true and well-supported.
"My lord, my lord - -"
"I won't listen to you."
"No? Come on, brother, let's go! I want to speak."
"And some of us will get hurt because of it."
"Look, look! Here comes the man we were looking for."
"Now, sir, what’s happening?"
"Hello, my lord."
Welcome, sir; you are just about to stop a fight.
We almost had our noses broken by two old men without any teeth.
"Leonato and his brother. What do you think? If we had fought, I’m afraid we would have been too young to win."
In a fake fight, there’s no real bravery. I came to find you both.
We've been looking for you because we're really sad and want to feel better. Can you help us with your cleverness?
"It's in my sword holder; should I take it out?"
"Do you keep your cleverness close by?"
"Can I whisper something to you?"
"Please keep me safe from a challenge!"
You have the courage to act, but if you don't treat me fairly, I'll call you a coward. You have harmed a kind lady, and her death will weigh on your conscience. I want to hear from you.

Goodbye, boy, you know how I feel. Thank you for your kindness, but I have to leave. Your brother has run away, and you have harmed a sweet and innocent lady. As for Lord Lackbeard, I will see him again, and until then, I wish him peace.
"He is serious."
"I really mean it, and I promise you, it's because I love Beatrice."
"And has dared you."
"Very truly."
"Wait, let me be alone: gather your strength, my heart, and feel sad. Didn't he say my brother ran away?"
Come here, sir. If justice can't control you, then she won't have any more reasons to consider. If you're a lying hypocrite, you need to be careful.
"What's going on? Two of my brother's men are tied up? Is Borachio one of them?"
"Listen to what they did wrong, my lord."
"Officers, what have these men done wrong?"
"Well, sir, they have told lies, spoken untruths, spread rumors, and wrongly accused a lady. In short, they are dishonest people."
Who have you upset, friends, that you have to explain yourselves? This smart officer is too tricky to understand. What did you do wrong?

Dear Prince, I tricked you without you knowing. While you didn't see the truth, some silly people did and heard me admit that your brother made me lie about Lady Hero. You saw me flirting with Margaret while pretending to be Hero, and you shamed her when you were supposed to marry her. Because of my lies and my master's, the lady is dead, and all I want now is the punishment I deserve.
"Doesn't this speech feel powerful and strong to you?"
I drank poison while he was saying it.
"Did my brother tell you to do this?"
"Yes, and they paid me well for doing it."
He is made of lies and trickery, and he has run away because of this bad deed.

"Sweet Hero! Now I see you just like I loved you before. DOGBERRY: Come on, let's take the people who are complaining. By now our town clerk has told Signior Leonato about it: and guys, remember to say, when it's the right time and place, that I’m a fool."
Look, here comes Mr. Leonato and the gravekeeper. Leonato and Antonio enter with the gravekeeper.
Which one is the bad guy? I want to see his eyes so I can stay away from anyone who looks like him. Which one is he?
"If you want to see who hurt you, look at me."
Are you the person who has killed my innocent child with your words?
"Yes, it's just me."

"No, that's not true, you liar. Here are two good men standing, while a third has run away, and he was involved too. Thank you, Princes, for my daughter's death; remember it with your great actions; it was done bravely, if you think about it."
I don’t know how to ask you to be patient, but I have to talk. You can decide how to punish me for my mistake, but I didn’t mean to do anything wrong.
I swear, I feel the same way. But to make this kind old man happy, I would do anything he asks me to.

I can't ask you to make my daughter come back to life, which is impossible. But please tell everyone in Messina how innocent she was when she died. If you love me, come to my house tomorrow morning. Since you can't be my son-in-law, be my nephew instead. My brother has a daughter who looks just like my dead child, and she will inherit everything from us. Treat her like you would have treated your cousin, and that will end my desire for revenge.
Oh kind sir, your kindness makes me cry! I accept your offer and will let go of poor Claudio from now on.
I will wait for you to come tomorrow; for now, I will say goodbye. This bad man will be brought to Margaret, who I think was involved in all this trouble, hired by your brother.
No, she wasn't, and she didn't know what she was saying when she talked to me, but she has always been good and honest in everything I know about her.
Also, sir, this person here, the one who did something wrong, called me a donkey; please remember that when deciding his punishment. Thank you for your help and hard work.
You speak like a very grateful and respectful young person, and I thank God for you.
"Here’s a reward for your hard work."
"May God protect the foundation!"
"Go, I release you from your prisoner, and I thank you."
"I'm leaving a really bad person with you, and I ask you to deal with him yourself, so others can see. Take care!"
Goodbye, lords, until tomorrow morning.
Goodbye, my friends, we’ll see you tomorrow.
"We won't give up."
"Tonight I'll be sad with Hero."
"Bring these guys here. We need to talk to Margaret about how she got to know this bad man."
"Good Ursula, wake up my cousin Beatrice and ask her to get up."
"I will, my lady."
"And ask her to come here."
"Okay."
Honestly, I think your other collar looks better.
"No, please good Meg, I'll wear this."
"I promise it's not that good, and I'm sure your cousin will agree."
"Good morning, cousin."
"Good morning, dear Hero."
What's wrong? Are you talking in a sad way?
"I feel really out of sorts. It's almost five o'clock, cousin, you should be ready. Honestly, I feel very sick -- oh dear! MARGARET For a hawk, a horse, or a husband?"
"Starting with the letter H, here comes Ursula again."
"Ma'am, please step back! The Prince, the Count, Benedick, Don John, and all the gentlemen in town have come to take you to church."
"Help me get ready, dear cousin, good Meg, good Ursula."
Count Claudio will marry Leonato's daughter.
"Yes, my lord, but I can get over it."
"How can you stop this wedding?"
"Not honestly, my lord, but secretly so that no one will see my dishonesty."
"Please show me quickly how to do it."
I believe I told you last year how much I like Margaret, Hero's maid.
"I remember."
I can ask her to watch out of her lady's window at any time during the night.
"What good is it if it ends this marriage?"
You have the power to fix this. Go to your brother the Prince and tell him he has hurt his honor by marrying Claudio to someone like Hero, who is not good.
"What evidence do I need to show for that?"
This is enough to hurt the Prince, upset Claudio, ruin Hero, and kill Leonato. Are you expecting anything else to happen?
I will do anything just to annoy them.
Go find a good time to get Don Pedro and Count Claudio alone. Tell them you know Hero loves me and make them believe that she is unfaithful, so they will doubt her before the wedding.
No matter how bad this turns out, I will make it happen. Be smart about how you do this, and I will pay you a thousand coins.
If you keep accusing me, I won't be embarrassed by my cleverness.
"What do you want from me, honest neighbor?"
"Well, sir, I want to talk to you about something important."
"Please be quick, because I have a lot to do right now."
"Yes, this is it, sir."
"Yes, it really is, sir."
"What is it, my friends?"
Well, sir, our watch tonight, without you here, has caught a couple of really bad guys in Messina.
He's a nice old man, sir, and he'll keep talking; as they say, "When you get old, you lose your cleverness." It's quite a sight, I swear! Well said, my friend.
"I have to go now."
"One word, sir: our watch has caught two important people, and we want them questioned this morning. LEONATO: You question them yourself and bring me the answers; I'm in a big hurry."
"It will be enough."
Have some wine before you leave. Goodbye!
"Go, my friend, and tell Francis Seacole to bring his pen and ink to the jail: we need to question these men now."
"And we need to do it carefully."
"We won't hold back on clever ideas, I promise you; this will make some of them give up. Just have the smart writer write down our punishment, and meet me at the jail."
"Wasn't Count John here for dinner?"
"I didn't see him."
That man looks so grumpy! Every time I see him, I feel upset for an hour afterwards.
I promise you, niece, you will never find a husband if you keep talking like that.
Honestly, she's too mean.
Being very mean is worse than just mean. I will make sure not to make things worse, because they say that God gives a mean cow short horns, but to a cow that is too mean, He gives none at all.
If you are too mean, God won't give you any trouble.
It's fair if he doesn't give me a husband, and I pray for that every morning and evening. Oh, I couldn't stand a husband with a beard! I'd rather sleep on the floor.
You might find a husband who doesn't have a beard.

What should I do with him? Should I dress him like a girl? A guy with a beard is older than a boy, and a guy without a beard is younger than a man; I don’t want someone older than a boy or someone younger than a man. So, I’ll just take a little money and lead his monkeys to a bad place.
"Fine, then go to hell!"

"No, I’ll go to the gate, and the Devil will tell me, 'Go to heaven, Beatrice, this place isn’t for you girls.' So I’ll give up my troubles and head to Saint Peter, where he’ll show me where the single men are, and we’ll be as happy as can be."
"Okay, niece, I hope you will listen to your dad."
Yes, it's my cousin's job to bow and say, "Father, if it pleases you": but still, cousin, if he’s not good-looking, he should bow again and say, "Father, if it pleases me."
Well, niece, I hope to see you married someday.
"Not until God makes people out of something other than dirt."
"Daughter, remember what I said: if the Prince asks you for that, you know what to say. The party guests are coming in, brother; make some space. Everyone put on their masks."
"Will you take a walk with your friend?"
You walk gently, look nice, and don’t say anything; I’m yours while we walk, especially when I leave.
"Whisper if you talk about love. They move away."
"I know you, you are Mr. Antonio."
In short, I don't exist.
"I can tell it's you by how you move your head."
To be honest, I’m pretending to be like him.
You could never hurt him so much - well, unless you were the one who did it.
In a nutshell, I don't exist.
Come on, do you think I don't recognize you because you're so clever? Goodness can't stay hidden. Stop pretending, it's obvious who you are.
"Will you not say who told you that?"
"No, please forgive me."
"Will you please tell me who you are?"
"Not right now."
Benedick said that I was rude and that I got my cleverness from a funny book.
"Who is he?"
"I know you know him pretty well."
"Not me, I promise."
"Did he never make you smile?"
"Please tell me, who is he?"

He's the Prince's clown, a really silly fool; his only talent is making up terrible lies. Only bad people like him, and he's not funny, just mean; he makes people laugh and then they get mad at him and hit him. I bet he's in jail; I wish he had come after me.
"When I meet the man, I'll tell him what you said."
"Come on, he’ll just make a few jokes about me. We need to follow the leaders."
"In everything good."
"No, if they cause any trouble, I'll turn back at the next corner. Let's dance. Then everyone leaves except Don John, Borachio, and Claudio."
I’m sure my brother likes Hero and has taken her father aside to talk about it.
"That’s Claudio: I can tell who he is by how he carries himself."
"Aren't you Mr. Benedick?"
"You know me well, it's me."
Sir, you are close to my brother in his feelings. He loves Hero; please help him see that she is not good enough for him.
How do you know he loves her?
"I heard him promise he loves her."
"I did too, and he promised he would marry her tonight."
"Come on, let's go to the party."

I speak for Benedick, but listen to this bad news for Claudio. It's true; the Prince is trying to win her for himself. Friendship stays strong in everything else except love. So, everyone in love should speak for themselves and not trust anyone else, because beauty can be tricky and makes people forget their loyalty. This happens all the time, and I didn't see it coming. Goodbye, Hero!
"Is that Count Claudio?"
"Yes, the same."
"Come on, will you go with me?"
"Where to?"
"Just go to the next willow tree and mind your own business, Count. The Prince has taken your Hero."
"I hope he is happy with her."
"Wow, that sounds like a truthful cattle seller: that's how they sell cows. But did you really think the Prince would treat you this way?"
Please, go away from me.
"Hey, now you're swinging wildly! It was the boy who took your food, and you'll just hit the post. CLAUDIO: If it can't be fixed, I'm leaving you."
"But my Lady Beatrice knows me and doesn't know me! The Prince's fool! Ha! Well, I'll get my revenge however I can."
"Hey, where's the Count? Did you see him?"
Honestly, my lord, I acted like Lady Fame. I found him here very sad, and I told him that you have the young lady's favor.
Beatrice is upset with you because the man who danced with her said you have treated her badly.

Oh, she treated me so badly that I couldn't take it anymore! She thought I was just a fool, making fun of me so much that I felt like I was being attacked by an army. Don't talk about her; she brings nothing but trouble and fear.
"Look, she's coming."
Will you ask me to do anything for you, even if it's far away? I'll go anywhere you want, but do you have nothing for me to do?
"I just want to be with you."
Oh no, sir, I really don't like this food! I can't stand my lady's chatter.
Come, lady, come, you've made Signior Benedick fall in love with you.
Yes, my lord, he borrowed it from me for a bit, and I gave him my love in return, even more than he gave me. But he tricked me out of it before, so you can say I’ve lost it.
"You have made him feel bad, lady, you have made him feel bad."
"I didn't want him to do that to me, my lord, because I might look foolish. I have brought Count Claudio, just like you asked."
"Why are you sad, Count?"
"I'm not sad, my lord."
"What's wrong? Are you sick?"
"Me neither, my lord."
The Count is not sad, sick, happy, or healthy; he is polite like an orange, but has a bit of jealousy in him.

I truly believe what you say is right, but if it is, then he is wrong. Claudio, I have asked for Hero's hand for you, and her father has agreed. Just tell me the wedding day, and I wish you happiness!
Count, please take my daughter and my wealth; the Duke has arranged the marriage.
"Talk now, Count, it's your turn."
Being quiet shows true happiness; I wouldn't be very happy if I could say how much. Lady, since you are mine, I am yours; I give myself to you and love that change.
"Talk, cousin, or if you can't, kiss him to make him quiet so he won't talk either."
Truly, lady, you have a happy heart.
Yes, my lord, I appreciate it, silly fool, it helps me worry less. My cousin whispers to him that he is in her heart.
"And she does, cousin."
Oh no, everyone is getting married but me, and I'm feeling left out. I might as well sit in a corner and cry, "I wish I had a husband!"
"Lady Beatrice, I will get you one."
"I would prefer to have one of your father's sons. Don't you have a brother like you? Your father had great husbands, if a girl could find them."
"Do you want me, lady?"
"No, my lord, I can't wear you all the time because you're too fancy for everyday use. But please forgive me, I was meant to be happy and not serious."
Your silence really bothers me, and being happy suits you best because, without a doubt, you were born to be cheerful.
"No, my lord, my mother cried, but then a star shone, and that's when I was born. Cousins, I wish you happiness!"
"Honestly, she's a cheerful lady."
